'''Priyanka Chopra''' ({{IPA-hns|pr<U+026A><U+02C8>j<U+0259><U+014B>ka<U+02D0> <U+02C8>t<U+0283>o<U+02D0>p<U+027D>a<U+02D0>|pron}}; born 18 July 1982)<ref name=bday1>{{cite web|title=Birthday Special: 30 Facts About Priyanka Chopra&nbsp;<U+2014> Page 1|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-birthday-special-priyanka-chopra/20120718.htm|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|date=18 July 2012|accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref><ref name=bday2>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Birthday-blast-Priyanka-Chopra-s-Top-30-moments-in-showbiz/Article1-890611.aspx |title=Birthday blast: Priyanka Chopra's Top 30 moments in showbiz |publisher=[[HT Media]]|work=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=17 July 2012 |accessdate=3 September 2012}}</ref> is an Indian actress, singer and songwriter. She was born to parents who were both army physicians. Due to their frequent reassignments, she grew up in many different cities in India, as well as spending a few years in the United States. Before starting her acting career, she gained fame after winning the [[Femina Miss India|Miss India]] and [[Miss World 2000|Miss World]] titles in 2000.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka admits lapse |url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2000/20001205/world.htm#9 |date=5 December 2000|accessdate=29 August 2009|author=[[Indo-Asian News Service]]|work=[[The Tribune]]}}</ref> During her career, Chopra has received one [[National Film Award]] for Best Actress, and [[Filmfare Awards]] in four distinct categories.

Making her acting debut with the 2002 [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] film ''Apuroopam'', Chopra later made her [[Bollywood]] debut with ''[[The Hero: Love Story of a Spy|The Hero]]'' in 2003. She followed that with the hit ''[[Andaaz]]'', for which she won a [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut]]. She subsequently earned critical acclaim for her performance in ''[[Aitraaz]]'' for which she earned a [[Filmfare Award for Best Performance in a Negative Role]] and appeared in the commercially successful projects ''[[Mujhse Shaadi Karogi]]'' (2004), ''[[Krrish]]'' (2006) and ''[[Don (2006 Hindi film)|Don]]'' (2006). The year 2008 marked the beginning of a new phase in Chopra's career, as her portrayal of a troubled model in the film ''[[Fashion (film)|Fashion]]'' earned her the [[National Film Award for Best Actress]] and the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]]. She was later noted for her performances in ''[[Kaminey]]'' (2009), ''[[What's Your Raashee?]]'' (2009), ''[[7 Khoon Maaf]]'' (2011), which garnered her the [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress]], and for ''[[Barfi!]]'' (2012). Having done so, Chopra established herself as one of the leading contemporary actresses in Bollywood.<ref>{{cite web|author=Masand, Rajeev|title=Priyanka on her best role|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/to-catch-a-star-priyanka-on-her-best-role/98858-8.html|publisher=[[CNN-IBN]]|date=9 August 2009|accessdate=16 August 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ten Best Bollywood Actresses of 2005 |url=http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2005/dec/23yend4.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|date=23 December 2005|accessdate=16 August 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Powerlist: Top Bollywood Actresses |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/25sd10.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|date=25 August 2006|accessdate=26 August 2006}}</ref>

Besides acting in films, Chopra has performed on television and stage shows. She has written columns in national Indian newspapers, and is active in charity work. She is regarded as one of most popular and attractive celebrities in India, and has many endorsement deals. In 2011, she signed a [[sound recording and reproduction|recording]] agreement with [[Universal Music Group]] and [[DesiHits]] to release her first music album. The first single, "[[In My City]]", was released in September 2012.

==Early life and pageantry==
Priyanka Chopra was born on 18 July 1982, in [[Jamshedpur]], India to Capt. Dr. Ashok Chopra and Dr. Madhu Chopra, both [[physicians]] by profession in the [[Indian Army]].<ref name=bday1/> She has a brother, Siddharth, who is seven years younger than her.<ref>{{cite web|title=In pics: Meet Priyanka Chopra's family |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/photogallery/7417-14.html |publisher=CNN-IBN|date=14 Septemver 2012|accessdate=11 October 2012}}</ref> Actress [[Parineeti Chopra]] is her cousin.<ref>{{cite news|title=Divas vs Parineeti Chopra |url=http://www.tehelka.com/story_main52.asp?filename=hub190512Divas.asp |publisher=''[[Tehelka]]''|date=19 May 2012|accessdate=2 September 2012}}</ref> Since her father was in the army, her family frequently moved from one city to another during her schooling days. In an interview with ''[[Daily News and Analysis]]'', Chopra said that she did not mind travelling regularly and shifting schools. She welcomed it as a new experience and a way to discover the multicultural Indian society.<ref>{{cite news|title=Diwali is always a fun time: Priyanka Chopra|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/mobile/report.php?n=1201128&p=0|author=Guha, Aniruddha|publisher=''[[Daily News and Analysis]]''|date=25 October 2008|accessdate=2 September 2012}}</ref> Places where she lived as a child include Jamshedpur, [[Delhi]], [[Pune]], [[Lucknow]], [[Bareilly]], [[Ladakh]], [[Chandigarh]] and [[Ambala]].<ref name=inspire>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra first single inspired by her life |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Music/Priyanka-Chopra-first-single-inspired-by-her-life/Article1-925965.aspx|publisher=''Hindustan Times''|date=7 September 2012|accessdate=16 September 2012}}</ref>

Chopra studied at [[La Martiniere Lucknow|La Martiniere Girls' School]] in Lucknow and St. Maria Goretti College in Bareilly.<ref name=nst>{{cite news |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-126612847.html |title=Chopra's star quality |work=[[New Straits Times]] |author=Henry, Wilson |date=23 July 2006 |accessdate=5 December 2012}}{{subscription required|via=Highbeam}}</ref> She subsequently re-located to the U.S. where she attended school in [[Newton, Massachusetts]] and [[Cedar Rapids, Iowa]].<ref name=spin>{{cite news|title=From Bollywood to will.i.am: Priyanka Chopra's Big Shot|url=http://www.spin.com/articles/priyanka-chopra-actress-singer-album-william|publisher=''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]''|author=Pandya, Sameer |date=12 October 2012|accessdate=4 December 2012}}</ref> She later recalled, "It was a huge culture shock for me when I went to study for three years in Boston at the age of 13."<ref>{{cite web|title=When Priyanka Chopra slept in a <U+2018>cage<U+2019>|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_when-priyanka-chopra-slept-in-a-cage_1285654|publisher=''Daily News and Analysis''|accessdate=2 September 2012}}</ref> While in Boston, she participated in several theatre productions, and studied [[Western classical music]], chorus and [[choir]] singing, as well as [[Kathak]] dance.<ref name=celluloid>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2001/12/14/stories/2001121400720200.htm |title=From beauty pageant to celluloid |publisher=''[[The Hindu]]'' |date=14 December 2001 |accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref> Having completed the tenth class, Chopra returned to India and finished her high school education at [[Army Public School]] in Bareilly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armyschoolbareilly.com/alumni.html |title=Army School Alumni|publisher=Army School Bareilly |date=|accessdate=4 December 2012}}</ref> During this period she won a local beauty pageant called "May Queen".<ref name=ti1>{{cite news|title=Granny brought up Priyanka |url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2000/20001202/main3.htm#3 |publisher=''Tribune India''|date=1 December 2000|accessdate=2 September 2012}}</ref> She was in college planning to study either [[Engineering]] or [[Psychology]], but left after winning the [[Miss World]] pageant.<ref name=nst/><ref name=ti1/>

Chopra's mother enrolled her for the [[Femina Miss India]] contest,<ref name=MeetPC>{{cite news |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2004/jul/29priyanka.htm |title=Meet Priyanka Chopra |publisher=Rediff.com |date= |accessdate=7 April 2011}}</ref> in which she came second at the 2000 competition, winning the Femina Miss India World title.<ref name=fmi>{{cite news |url=http://feminamissindia.indiatimes.com/Archives/International-Winners/articleshow/msid-5931192,curpg-2.cms |title=International Pageant Winners |publisher=''The Times of India'' |date= |accessdate=15 March 2012}}</ref> She was subsequently sent to the Miss World pageant, where she was crowned [[Miss World 2000]], along with [[List of Miss World Continental Queen of Beauty winners|Miss World Continental Queen of Beauty <U+2212> Asia & Oceania]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rediff.com/news/2000/nov/30world.htm|title=Priyanka Chopra is Miss World 2000|publisher=Rediff.com|date=30 November 2000|accessdate=2 August 2006}}</ref> In the same year, her Miss India co-winners [[Lara Dutta]] and [[Dia Mirza]], won the [[Miss Universe]] and [[Miss Asia Pacific]] crowns respectively, in a rare triple victory for one country.<ref name=winners>{{cite news |url=http://feminamissindia.indiatimes.com/archives/1991-2000/articleshow/5022005.cms |title=Miss India Winner 2000&nbsp;<U+2013> 1991 |publisher=''The Times of India'' |date= |accessdate=3 December 2012}}</ref> When Chopra won the Miss World crown, she became the fifth Indian woman to win the title, and the fourth Indian woman to do so in a span of seven years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra Miss World 2000 |url=http://hindu.com/2000/12/02/stories/01020004.htm |author=Suroor, Hasan |publisher=''The Hindu''|date=1 December 2000|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref><ref name=winners/> She stated that the Miss World title brought her recognition and fame, and then she started getting offers for film roles.<ref name=celluloid/>

==Acting career==

===Debut and early work (2002<U+2013>03)===
Priyanka Chopra made her acting debut in the 2002 [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film ''Apuroopam''.<ref>{{cite web|title=T-town: The perfect launchpad for aspiring actors|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-29/news-interviews/30213237_1_telugu-film-film-industry-hindi-film|author=Kavirayani, Suresh|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=29 September 2011|accessdate=29 November 2012}}</ref> She then appeared in a [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film ''[[Thamizhan]]'' playing the role of Priya, the love interest of the protagonist in the film played by [[Joseph Vijay|Vijay]]. The film was praised for its wit and dialogues, although the depth of Chopra's character was seen as lacking.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/04/19/stories/2002041900820203.htm |title=Thamizhan|work=The Hindu|date=19 April 2002|accessdate=19 March 2010|location=Chennai, India}}</ref> In 2003, she appeared in her first Bollywood film, opposite [[Sunny Deol]] and [[Preity Zinta]] in the [[Anil Sharma]] film  ''[[The Hero: Love Story of a Spy]]''. She played a supporting role as a doctor named Shaheen in the film. Despite being one of the highest grossing films of that year,<ref name="Box Office 2003">{{cite web|title=Box Office 2003|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=209&catName=MjAwMw==|publisher=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=26 October 2010}}</ref>  it received mixed reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Hero: Love Story of a Spy (2003) |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/10002625-hero/ |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=18 October 2012}}</ref> Though Chopra played the second female lead, her acting performance did get her noticed.<ref name=bday2/> Later that year she appeared in [[Raj Kanwar]]'s  ''[[Andaaz]]'', playing the character of Jiya who falls in love with Raj Malhotra, played by [[Akshay Kumar]]. The film was a success at the box office,<ref name="Box Office 2003"/> earning her a [[Filmfare Best Female Debut Award]]<ref name=ff1>{{cite web|title=Awards 2003&nbsp;<U+2013> The 51st Filmfare Awards |url=http://filmfareawards.indiatimes.com/articleshow/512087.cms|publisher=''[[The Times of India]]''|accessdate=2 September 2012}}</ref> and a nomination for [[Filmfare Best Supporting Actress Award]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Nominees for the 49th Manikchand Filmfare Awards 2003|url=http://filmfareawards.indiatimes.com/articleshow/477096.cms?&fright=1&right=1|publisher=''The Times of India''|accessdate=2 September 2012}}</ref> Ashish Magotra writing for [[Rediff.com]] said of her role, "Priyanka Chopra alone clicks with the audience, thanks to her skimpy outfits."<ref>{{cite web|author=Magotra, Ashish|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/may/23andaaz.htm|title='Andaaz': Flight to boredom|publisher=Rediff.com|date=23 May 2003|accessdate=19 March 2010}}</ref>

===Breakthrough and setbacks (2004<U+2013>08)===
Her next films which released in 2004, ''[[Plan (film)|Plan]]'', ''[[Kismat (2004 film)|Kismat]]'', and ''[[Asambhav]]'' performed poorly at the box office.<ref name=BOI2004/><ref>{{cite web|title=Bollywood Box Office Report |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2004/jul/27box.htm |publisher=Rediff.com|date=27 July 2004|accessdate=16 October 2012}}</ref> Later that year she appeared in [[David Dhawan]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Mujhse Shaadi Karogi]]'' playing the role of a young fashion designer Rani along with [[Salman Khan]] and Akshay Kumar. The film turned out to be the third-highest grossing film of that year.<ref name=BOI2004>{{cite web|title=Box Office 2004|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=210&catName=MjAwNA==|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=26 October 2010}}</ref> She next starred in [[Abbas-Mustan]]'s thriller ''[[Aitraaz]]'' alongside Kumar and [[Kareena Kapoor]]. It was her first negative role and her performance was critically acclaimed.<ref>{{cite web|author=Adarsh, Taran|title=Movie Review: Aitraaz|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/200448|publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|date=11 November 2004|accessdate=9 September 2012}}</ref> Film critic Subhash K. Jha noted, "A star is born! As the predatory social-climbing seductress who can go to any length to satiate her lust for life, Priyanka Chopra rocks the scene like never before. The film is undoubtedly a triumph for Priyanka Chopra. With half a smile, a twitch of her lip and a movement of her eyebrow she seems to slip into her man-eater's role with captivating ease".<ref>{{cite web|author=Jha, Subhash K.|url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/reviews/aitraaz.asp |title=Movie Review : <U+2018>Aitraaz<U+2019>|publisher=Indo-Asian News Service|date=12 November 2004|accessdate=29 November 2010}}</ref> She earned a [[Filmfare Award for Best Performance in a Negative Role]] (also known as the Best Villain Award),<ref name=ff2>{{cite news|title=No time to enjoy the success: Priyanka Chopra |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/No-time-to-enjoy-the-success-Priyanka-Chopra/Article1-787309.aspx |work=Hindustan Times |date=26 December 2011 |accessdate=5 December 2012}}</ref> becoming the second and last female actor to win the award after [[Kajol]] (the category has been retired since 2008). She also received a second nomination for Filmfare Best Supporting Actress Award for the role.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nominees of 50th Filmfare Awards|url=http://filmfareawards.indiatimes.com/articleshow/msid-1021384,curpg-3.cms|publisher=''The Times of India''|accessdate=2 September 2012}}</ref>

In 2005, she starred in six films. Four of them, ''[[Blackmail (2005 film)|Blackmail]]'', ''[[Karam (film)|Karam]]'', ''[[Yakeen (2005 film)|Yakeen]]'' and ''[[Barsaat (2005 film)|Barsaat]]'' failed to do well.<ref name=BOI2005/> However, her performance in ''Yakeen'' garnered good reviews from critics.<ref>{{cite web|title=Yakeen: Predictable fare|publisher=Rediff.com|url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2005/jul/01yakeen.htm|date=1 June 2005|accessdate=20September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Yakeen Review|author=Adarsh, Taran|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/review/id/538457|date=1 July 2005|accessdate=3 September 2012}}</ref> Her other two 2005 releases, ''[[Waqt: The Race Against Time]]'' and ''[[Bluffmaster!]]'' were moderately successful at the box office.<ref name=BOI2005>{{cite web|title=Box Office 2005|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=211&catName=MjAwNQ==|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=19 October 2010}}</ref> Subhash K Jha wrote about her performance in ''Bluffmaster!'', "Chopra has little to do. But she does it with eye-catching aplomb."<ref>{{cite web|title=Bluffmaster! review|author=Jha, Subhash|url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/reviews/bluffmaster.asp|accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref> In 2006, Chopra starred in [[Rakesh Roshan]]'s ''[[Krrish]]'' which was a sequel to the 2004 sci-fi film ''[[Koi... Mil Gaya]]''. She shared the screen with [[Hrithik Roshan]] and [[Rekha]]. The film was declared a blockbuster and was one of the highest grossing films of the year.<ref name=boi06/> She also appeared in ''[[Aap Ki Khatir (2006 film)|Aap Ki Khatir]]'' opposite [[Akshaye Khanna]] and [[Dino Morea]]. Her last release was [[Farhan Akhtar]]'s ''[[Don (2006 Hindi film)|Don]]'', alongside [[Shahrukh Khan]] which was a remake of the [[Don (1978 film)|1978 film of the same name]]. She was cast to play Roma, a role which was played by [[Zeenat Aman]] in the original movie. Chopra and Khan underwent special martial arts training for their roles in the movie and both performed their own stunts.<ref>{{cite news|title=Little film action for female stunt artistes|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-05-01/mumbai/29492819_1_stunts-film-industry-action-scenes|publisher=''The Times of India''|author=Dubey, Bharti |date=1 May 2011|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> Upon release, the film was generally well received both in India and abroad. A week after its theatrical run, Box Office India declared the film a hit in India, and a "blockbuster" overseas.<ref name=boi06>{{cite web|title=Box Office 2006|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=212&catName=MjAwNg==|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=26 October 2010}}</ref> Aside from that, she made special appearances in three other films that year.

In 2007, she appeared in [[Nikhil Advani]]'s ensemble piece ''[[Salaam-e-Ishq: A Tribute to Love]]''. Despite a promising opening, the movie was a financial failure.<ref>{{cite web|title=Box Office 2007|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=214&catName=MjAwNw==|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=26 October 2010}}</ref> Chopra was criticized for her performance in the film, with Lidia Ostepeev of Planet Bollywood calling it "forced" and "overly exaggerated".<ref>{{cite web|title=Salaam-E-Ishq movie review|author=Ostepeev, Lidia |url=http://www.planetbollywood.com/displayReview.php?id=012507054059 |publisher=Planet Bollywood|date=24 January 2007|accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref> Her next release, the much-delayed ''[[Big Brother (film)|Big Brother]]'', also failed at the box-office.<ref>{{cite web|title=Metro, GBBB open poorly|url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2007/may/14box.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|date=14 May 2007|accessdate=16 September 2012}}</ref> In 2008, Chopra acted in six films. Her first four films, ''[[Love Story 2050]]'', ''[[God Tussi Great Ho]]'', ''[[Chamku (film)|Chamku]]'' and ''[[Drona (2008 film)|Drona]]'', were critical and commercial failures.<ref name="BO-08">{{cite web|publisher=Box Office India|title=Box Office 2008|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=215&catName=MjAwOA==|accessdate=7 August 2009}}</ref> During this time, Chopra received mixed reviews for her performances.<ref>{{cite web|title=Masand's Verdict: Love Story 2050|author=Masand, Rajeev|publisher=CNN-IBN|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/love-story-2050-partpredictable-partgobbledygook/68318-8.html|date=5 July 2008|accessdate=18 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Kasmi, Nikhat |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/God-Tussi-Great-Ho/movie-review/3369194.cms |title=God Tussi Great Ho&nbsp;<U+2014> ''The Times of India'' |publisher=''The Times of India'' |date=15 August 2008 |accessdate=17 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54382 |title=Chamku (2008) Hindi Movie Critic Review By Taran Adarsh |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |date=29 August 2008 |accessdate=17 October 2012}}</ref>

===Critical success (2008<U+2013>11)===
{{Quote box|width=30em|align=right|quote="I will give full credit to Madhur Bhandarkar and the crew. I am really honoured. National Award is the biggest honour of our country and I am really honoured to have received one."|source=<U+2014>Chopra on winning the National Film Award for Best Actress for her performance in ''Fashion'' (2008)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/Ndtv-Show-Special-Story.aspx?ID=76&StoryID=ENTEN20100127357 |title=Priyanka Chopra bags National award for Fashion |publisher=[[NDTV]] |date=23 January 2010|accessdate=7 September 2012}}</ref>}}
After a series of flops, Chopra was cast in [[Madhur Bhandarkar]]'s ''[[Fashion (film)|Fashion]]'' (2008), for the lead role of Meghna Mathur. Revolving around the fashion world through Chopra's role of an ambitious model, the film was a critical success. Her performance in the film was appreciated and earned her several awards for Best Actress including the [[National Film Award for Best Actress]],<ref name="NDTV">{{cite web|title=V K Murthy, Priyanka Chopra receive National Awards |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/national-awards-given-away-to-vk-murthy-priyanka-chopra-bala/20100319.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|date=19 March 2010|accessdate=7 September 2012}}</ref><ref name=nat>{{cite news|title=National Film Awards: Priyanka gets best actress, 'Antaheen' awarded best film|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-01-23/india/28125140_1_national-film-awards-hindi-film-film-on-social-issues|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=23 January 2010|accessdate=23 January 2010}}</ref> the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]],<ref name=ff3>{{cite news|title=Filmfare: 'Jodha...' bags 5, Priyanka, Hrithik shine|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/specials/filmfare/Filmfare-Jodha-bags-5-Priyanka-Hrithik-shine/articleshow/4205152.cms|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=1 March 2009|accessdate=1 March 2009}}</ref> and the [[IIFA Award for Best Actress]].<ref>{{cite web|title=IIFA 2009 Award Winners |url=http://www.iifa.com/web07/showcase/2009-winnerslist.htm |publisher=[[International Indian Film Academy Awards|IIFA]]|date=|accessdate=5 December 2012}}</ref> This has been called her coming-of-age film, and a turning point in her career.<ref>{{cite news|title=OVER THE YEARS: From Priyanka to Pee Cee|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/OVER-THE-YEARS-From-Priyanka-to-Pee-Cee/Article1-929947.aspx |work=Hindustan Times|author=Marwah, Navdeep |date=14 September 2012|accessdate=4 December 2012}}</ref> [[Rajeev Masand]] wrote, "Chopra turns in a respectable performance, one that will inevitably go down as her best."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masands-verdict-fashion-no-real-expose/77189-8.html |title=Masand's Verdict: Fashion, no real expose |author=Masand, Rajeev|publisher=CNN-IBN |date=1 November 2008 |accessdate=30 November 2012}}</ref> Chopra's final release of the year was [[Tarun Mansukhani]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Dostana (2008 film)|Dostana]]'' alongside [[Abhishek Bachchan]] and [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]]. The film explores the story of two men who pretend to be gay, so that they can rent an apartment from an older lady. Both the men fall in love with the same girl, their roommate, but are unable to express their feelings because she is related to the old landlady. The film was a financial success and went on to become the eight-highest grossing film at the Indian box office in 2008.<ref name="BO-08"/> Chopra received positive reviews for her performance<ref>{{cite news|title=Review: Dostana|work=Hindustan Times|author=Mohamed, Khalid |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Review-Dostana/Article1-351544.aspx|date=14 November 2008|accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref> and her look in the film.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dostana, a barrel of laughs|author=Masand, Rajeev|publisher=CNN-IBN|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masands-verdict-dostana-a-barrel-of-laughs/78183-8-17.html|date=14 November 2008|accessdate=19 November 2010}}</ref>

In 2009, she appeared in [[Vishal Bhardwaj]]'s caper thriller ''[[Kaminey]]'' alongside [[Shahid Kapoor]], playing the role of a feisty [[Marathi people|Marathi]] girl named Sweety. The film was a critical and commercial success. Her performance received positive reviews  with [[Taran Adarsh]] describing it as "first-rate". He further stated, "She's so much in sync with her character... [and] gets the Maharashtrian accent perfect".<ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey Review|author=Adarsh, Taran|publisher=oneindia.in |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/reviews/2009/kaminey-review-130809.html|date=13 August 2009|accessdate=3 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kaminey Review|author=Chopra, Anupama |publisher=NDTV|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_Review.aspx?id=416 |date=14 August 2009|accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref> Her work in the film brought her several awards and nominations including a second Filmfare Award for Best Actress nomination<ref>{{cite web|url=http://photogallery.indiatimes.com/awards/filmfare-awards/Best-Actress-for-Kaminey/articleshow/5499483.cms |title=Priyanka Chopra- Best Actress for 'Kaminey' |publisher=''The Times of India'' |date=25 January 2010 |accessdate=17 October 2012}}</ref> and a second consecutive [[Apsara Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role]] after ''Fashion''.<ref>{{cite web|title=5th Apsara Awards |url=http://www.apsaraawards.org/5th_apsara_awards_winners.html |publisher=[[Apsara Awards]]|date=|accessdate=3 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=4th Apsara Awards |url=http://www.apsaraawards.org/4th_apsara_awards_winners.html |publisher=Apsara Awards|date=|accessdate=3 December 2012}}</ref> She subsequently appeared in [[Ashutosh Gowariker]]'s romantic comedy ''[[What's Your Raashee?]]'', a film for which Chopra was reportedly being considered for inclusion in the ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' book for being the first actress in cinema history to portray 12 distinct characters in one film.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra may find a place in Guinness Book |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2009-09-07/news/28443127_1_priyanka-chopra-guinness-book-actress |publisher=''Economic Times''|date=7 September 2009|accessdate=2 September 2012}}</ref> The film itself was a financial and critical failure,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2009/dec/15/priyanka-chopra-on-whats-your-rashee.htm |title=Priyanka: Failure of Raashee broke my heart&nbsp;<U+2014> Rediff.com Movies |publisher=Rediff.com |date=15 December 2009 |accessdate=17 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masands-movie-review-whats-your-raashee-epicsize-failure/102198-8.html |title=Masand's Verdict: What's Your Raashee boring |author=Masand, Rajeev|publisher=CNN-IBN |date=26 September 2009 |accessdate=17 October 2012}}</ref> but Chopra's performance was appreciated by the critics.<ref>{{cite web|title=What's Your Rashee&nbsp;<U+2014> The Review |author=Jha, Subhash K |url=http://www.ibosnetwork.com/newsmanager/templates/template1.aspx?a=21847&z=2 |publisher=IBOS Network|date=25 September 2009|accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref> Sukanya Verma in a review for Rediff.com wrote, "Priyanka Chopra transforms into 12 new skins with astonishing distinction, voice and spirit. The actress reinvents herself into this unique individual every single time ranging from batty, bashful and boisterous. This is simply her show."<ref>{{cite web|title=It's Priyanka Chopra's show all the way|author=Verma, Sukanya |publisher=Rediff.com|url=http://movies.rediff.com/review/2009/sep/25/review-whats-your-raashee.htm|date=25 September 2009|accessdate=12 January 2012}}</ref> Chopra was working so hard shooting this and other films, travelling for endorsements, performing at live shows, including at the Miss India pageant, that she passed out and was admitted to the hospital while filming ''What's Your Raashee?''.<ref>{{cite web|author=Shah, Kunal M |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-04-13/news-interviews/28026084_1_priyanka-first-priyanka-chopra-s-homepage-acute-stomach-infection |title=Overworked Priyanka in hospital! |publisher=''The Times of India''|date=13 April 2009 |accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref>

In 2010, Chopra appeared in [[Jugal Hansraj|Jugal Hansraj's]] ''[[Pyaar Impossible!]]'' opposite [[Uday Chopra]], where she portrayed the role of a beautiful college girl who eventually falls in love with a nerdy boy. The film was a commercial and critical failure.<ref name="all-India2010"/> Her next release, [[Siddharth Anand]]'s ''[[Anjaana Anjaani]]'' alongside [[Ranbir Kapoor]], got a good initial response at the box office,<ref name="all-India2010">{{cite web|title=All India 2010|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=366&catName=MjAxMA==|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=25 March 2011}}</ref> but was not well received by the critics. She received positive to mixed comments from critics for her performance.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anjaana Anjaani: Moview Review by Komal Nahta|author=Nahata, Komal |url=http://www.radiosargam.com/films/archives/65227/anjaana-anjaani-moview-review-komal-nahta.html|publisher=[[Radio Sargam]]|date=1 October 2010|accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Anjaana Anjaani|author=Chopra, Anupama |publisher=NDTV Movies|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_Review.aspx?id=552|date=1 October 2010|accessdate=9 September 2012}}</ref>

[[File:Priyanka Chopra Promoting 7 khoon Maaf.jpg|thumb|left|Chopra at the audio release of ''7 Khoon Maaf'' (2011). Her performance in the film received critical acclaim and among other wins, fetched her a Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress.|alt=An Indian woman in a light pink dress smiling towards the camera. She stands in front of a greenish background]]
Chopra's first release of 2011 was Vishal Bhardwaj's black comedy ''[[7 Khoon Maaf]]''. The film, based on [[Ruskin Bond]]'s short story ''Susanna's Seven Husbands'' saw Chopra portray the role of Susanna Anna-Marie Johannes, an [[Anglo-Indian]] woman who murders her seven husbands in an unending quest for love. The film was a commercial failure and received mixed response from the critics, however her performance received good reviews.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mayank Shekhar's review: 7 Khoon Maaf|author=Shekhar, Mayank |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/reviews/Mayank-Shekhar-s-review-7-Khoon-Maaf/Article1-664054.aspx|publisher=''Hindustan Times''|date=18 February 2011|accessdate=23 March 2012}}</ref> [[Nikhat Kazmi]] from ''The Times of India'' noted, "7 Khoon Maaf would undoubtedly end up as a milestone in Priyanka Chopra's career graph. The actor displays exquisite command over a complex character that is definitely a first in Indian cinema."<ref>{{cite web|author= Kazmi, Nikhat |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/7-Khoon-Maaf/movie-review/7516327.cms |title=7 Khoon Maaf |publisher=''The Times of India''|date=17 February 2011 |accessdate=24 February 2012}}</ref> Chopra eventually earned the [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress]] and a third Filmfare Award for Best Actress nomination along with a few other awards at other ceremonies.<ref name=ff4>{{cite news|title=Filmfare Awards: Ranbir Kapoor, Vidya Balan Named best actors|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/filmfare-awards-2012-ranbir-kapoor-vidya-balan-the-dirty-picture-rockstar/1/171157.html|publisher=''[[India Today]]''|date=30 January 2012|accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref>

Her next release was Farhan Akhtar's ''[[Don 2]]'' alongside Shahrukh Khan, in which she reprised her role of Roma. The film was a sequel to the 2006 action thriller ''Don''. Upon release, the film received mixed reviews, both in India<ref>{{cite web|title=Reviews for Don 2 |author= |url=http://www.reviewgang.com/movies/106-Don-2-movie-review |publisher=[[ReviewGang]]|date=|accessdate=4 December 2012}}</ref> and overseas.<ref>{{cite web|title=Critic Reviews for Don 2 |author= |url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/don-2/critic-reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]]|date=|accessdate=4 December 2012}}</ref> Chopra's performance received positive feedback from foreign critics, with the reviewer from ''[[The Express Tribune]]'' writing, "Chopra pulls of her role with aplomb and seems to be the perfect choice for an action heroine. As you watch her effortlessly beat up some thugs in the movie, you come to the realisation that she may be the first proper female action hero in Bollywood."<ref>{{cite news|title=Film review: Don 2 - making a killing|author=Mahmood, Rafay |publisher=''Express Tribune'' |url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/316484/film-review-don-2-making-a-killing/|date=9 January 2012|accessdate=3 September 2012}}</ref> A review carried by ''[[Divanee Magazine]]'' mentioned that Chopra surprises with a demeanor like that of ''[[Tomb Raider]]'''s [[Lara Croft]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The King is Back: Shahrukh Khan & Priyanka Chopra Sizzle in Don 2 (Movie Review)|author=Tabani, Saniya |publisher=''[[Divanee Magazine]]''|url=http://divanee.com/2011/12/23/the-king-is-back-shahrukh-khan-priyanka-chopra-sizzle-in-don-2-movie-review/|date=23 December 2012|accessdate=3 September 2012}}</ref> The film was a major success in India and a blockbuster overseas. It went on to break multiple box-office records in India and overseas, including the highest grossing Bollywood movie overseas in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Overseas Grossers 2011: DON 2 Tops Followed By RA.ONE|publisher=Box Office India |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3886&nCat=|date=4 January 2012|accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref>

===Recent work (2012<U+2013>present)===
In early 2012, Chopra became the first Bollywood actor to be signed by [[Creative Artists Agency]] (CAA), a prominent entertainment and sports agency headquartered in [[Los Angeles]]. The agency will handle her acting career in [[Hollywood]].<ref>{{cite news|title=CAA Signs Its First Bollywood Star|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/bollywood-actress-priyanka-chopra-signed-caa-287524|author=Bhushan, Nyay |publisher=''Hollywood Reporter''|date=2 July 2012|accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref> Her first release of the year was [[Karan Johar]]'s ''[[Agneepath (2012 film)|Agneepath]]'' alongside Hrithik Roshan, Sanjay Dutt and [[Rishi Kapoor]]. The film was a remake of the 1990 classic of the [[Agneepath (1990 film)|same name]]. Upon release, the film broke the [[List of highest-grossing Bollywood films#Opening day nett gross|highest opening day collections]] record and became a critical and commercial success.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/npages.php?page=shownews&articleid=3972&nCat= |title=Top Grossing Of All Time Days By A Single Film |publisher=Box Office India |date=28 January 2012 |accessdate=4 February 2012}}</ref> Her performance in the film was appreciated by most critics, such as Mayank Shekhar, who noted that she stood out in a male-centric movie.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Reviews/Mayank-Shekhar-s-review-Agneepath/Article1-802542.aspx|title=Mayank Shekhar's review: Agneepath|author=Shekhar, Mayank |work=Hindustan Times|date=26 January 2012|accessdate=10 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Agneepath/movie-review/11640168.cms|title=Agneepath movie review|work=The Times Of India|author=Ghosh, Avijit |date=26 January 2012 |accessdate=10 September 2012}}</ref> Her next release was [[Kunal Kohli]]'s  ''[[Teri Meri Kahaani]]'', a love story set in three different eras. The film opened to mixed reactions from critics, however Chopra's performance, and her on-screen chemistry with co-star Shahid Kapoor received good reviews. Sonia Chopra of [[Sify]] wrote, "Priyanka delivers a superb performance easily slipping in-and-out of the layered characters with dexterity."<ref>{{cite web|author=Chopra, Sonia |title=Teri Meri Kahaani review: A fun and hearty flick! |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/bollywood/review.php?id=15001477&ctid=5&cid=2425 |publisher=[[sify]]|accessdate=25 June 2012}}</ref> Taran Adarsh commented, "As the spirited Aradhana of 1910, the dazzling movie star Rukhsar of 1960, or the joyful Radha of 2012, Priyanka is a complete livewire in each of the acts."<ref>{{cite web|author=Adarsh, Taran |title= Teri Meri Kahaani Review|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/551914|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|date=22 Jun 2012|accessdate=25 June 2012}}</ref> However, despite the positive critical acclaim, the film failed to do well at the Indian box office, although was a moderate success in the overseas markets.<ref>{{cite web|title=Teri Meri Kahaani Box office collections |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/overdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4666&nCat= |publisher=Box Office India|date=11 July 2012|accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref>

[[File:Priyanka Chopra, Ranbir Kapoor at the launch of 'Barfi!' promo 05.jpg|thumb|right|Chopra with co-star Ranbir Kapoor promoting ''Barfi!'' in 2012|alt=An Indian man and woman sitting side-by-side and looking towards their right. The man wears a purple jacket while the woman wears a green dress.]]
In September 2012, Chopra featured in [[Anurag Basu]]'s ''[[Barfi!]]'' alongside Ranbir Kapoor and [[Ileana D'Cruz]]. She was cast as Jhilmil Chatterjee; an autistic girl who falls in love with a deaf and mute boy. While preparing for her role, Chopra visited mental institutions and spent time with autistic people. She said, "I had to research a little for the role because in India awareness about a condition such as autism is very low."<ref>{{cite web|title=What is Priyanka Chopra<U+2019>s Kottayam connection?|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/interview_what-is-priyanka-chopras-kottayam-connection_1740013|publisher=''Daily News and Analysis''|author=Prabhakaran, Mahalakshmi |date=12 September 2012|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref> The film opened to major critical acclaim<ref>{{cite web|title=Ranbir's Barfi garners rave reviews from film critics|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/features/2012/ranbir-barfi-reviews-ratings-film-critics-verdict-099467.html|publisher=oneindia.in|date=15 September 2012|accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref> and Chopra received unanimous praise for her portrayal, which several reviewers regarded as her best performance to date.<ref>{{cite web|author=Mukherjee, Madhureeta |title=Barfi! movie review|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Barfi/movie-review/16381742.cms|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=13 September 2012|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref> The ''[[Indo-Asian News Service]]'' review declared, "Priyanka Chopra as the autistic Jhilmil steals the show from Ranbir, if that's possible. Her inherent glamorous personality simply disappears into her character. We don't see the actress on screen at all! We see only Jhilmil who reminds us in a very pleasant way of [[Sridevi]] in ''[[Sadma]]''. This is one of the most flawless interpretations of a physical-psychological disability seen on celluloid."<ref>{{cite web|author=Indo-Asian News Service |title=Barfi! review|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_Review.aspx?id=743|publisher=NDTV|date=14 September 2012|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref> The film was chosen as [[List of Indian submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|India<U+2019>s official entry to the Oscars]] for the [[85th Academy Awards]] to be held in February 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=<U+2018>Barfi!<U+2019> to represent India at Oscars|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-23/news-interviews/34040221_1_rajmouli-s-eega-official-entry-anhey-ghorhey-da-daan|author=Dubey, Bharti |publisher=''The Times of India''|date=22 September 2012|accessdate=23 September 2012}}</ref>

As of November 2012, Chopra is set to appear in [[K. C. Bokadia]]'s much-delayed film ''[[Deewana Main Deewana]]''<ref>{{cite news|title=Finally, 'Deewana Main Deewana' set to hit theatres|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-10/news-interviews/33120058_1_movie-kc-bokadia-barfi|publisher=''The Times of India''|author=Mantri, Upasana |date=10 August 2012|accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref> and Rakesh Roshan's ''[[Krrish 3]]'', a sequel to the 2006 superhero film ''Krrish'' alongside Hrithik Roshan, [[Vivek Oberoi]] and [[Kangna Ranaut]]. Chopra will reprise her role of Priya in the film.<ref>{{cite web|author=Dubey, Rachana |title=Hrithik, Priyanka pair up again!|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Hrithik-Priyanka-pair-up-again/Article1-641497.aspx|work=Hindustan Times|date=22 December 2010|accessdate=22 December 2010}}</ref> She is filming [[Apoorva Lakhia]]'s ''[[Zanjeer(2013 film)|Zanjeer]]'', a remake of the 1973 [[Zanjeer|film of the same name]] opposite [[Ram Charan Teja]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Only I will do all of AB<U+2019>s remakes: Priyanka Chopra|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-06-25/news-interviews/32408593_1_remakes-agneepath-priyanka-chopra|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=25 June 2012|accessdate=30 August 2012}}</ref> Chopra has been signed on for [[Ali Abbas Zafar]]'s next ''Gunday'', which is set to start shooting in December 2012 <ref name=gd>{{cite news |title=Priyanka Chopra joins 'Gunday' gang |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-10-16/news-interviews/34497456_1_gunday-breakers-and-coal-thieves-bikram-and-bala |publisher=''The Times of India'' |date=16 October 2012|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1575554/Priyanka-Chopra-confirmed-for-YRFs-Gunday |title=Priyanka Chopra confirmed for YRF's Gunday |publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref> and [[Ekta Kapoor]]'s next production ''Milan Talkies'' to be directed by [[Tigmanshu Dhulia]].<ref name=mt>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra and Ekta Kapoor, the new friends in B-town|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Priyanka-Chopra-and-Ekta-Kapoor-the-new-friends-in-B-town/Article1-932376.aspx|author=Singh, Prashant |work=Hindustan Times|date=19 September 2012|accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-10-21/news-interviews/34607434_1_priyanka-chopra-milan-talkies-tigmanshu-dhulia |title=Ekta Kapooy teams up with Priyanka Chipra |work=The Times of India|date=21 October 2012|accessdate=25 Oct 2012}}</ref> She has also been confirmed for the lead role in [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]'s next production, a biopic based on the life of Olympic bronze medalist [[Boxing|boxer]] and [[World Amateur Boxing Championships|World Boxing Champion]] [[Mary Kom]]. In order to get into the skin of the character, Chopra will spend time with the boxer and undergo a rigorous boxing training for four months before shooting the film.<ref name=kom>{{cite web|author=Mumbai Mirror |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-11-28/news-interviews/35387423_1_priyanka-chopra-mary-kom-olympic-medallist |title=Priyanka Chopra to live like Mary Kom |publisher=''The Times of India'' |date=28 November 2012 |accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref>

==Other ventures==

===Music career===
Chopra is an avid fan of singing, and used it as her talent early in her pageantry career.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra<U+2019>s Foray Into Music with Lady Gaga<U+2019>s Management|url=http://divanee.com/2011/08/11/priyanka-chopras-foray-into-music-with-lady-gaga%E2%80%99s-management/|author=Tabani, Saniya |publisher=''Divanee Magazine''|date=11 August 2011|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref> She said of singing, "I love music as I grew up with it thanks to my father who loves to sing. We woke up every morning to music. I knew how to sing before I knew how to read."<ref>{{cite news|title=Berlin 2012: Priyanka Chopra Talks About Movies Transcending Cultural and Language Barriers (Q&A)|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/berlin-2012-priyanka-chopra-talks-291369|publisher=''Hollywood Reporter''|author=Bhushan,Nyay |date=15 February 2012|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> She made her singing debut by lending her voice to the song "Ullathai Killadhe" in the Tamil film ''Thamizhan'' (2002),<ref>{{cite news|title=Ushering in the new year|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/04/12/stories/2002041201610800.htm|publisher=''The Hindu''|date=12 April 2002|accessdate=30 August 2012}}</ref> after her director and co-star heard her singing in the sets.<ref>{{cite web|title=Eyecatchers&nbsp;<U+2014> She's Getting Vocal |url=http://archives.digitaltoday.in/indiatoday/20020128/eyecathers.html|publisher=Digital Today|work=India Today|date=28 January 2002|accessdate=16 September 2012}}</ref> Later, she declined an opportunity to sing "Tinka Tinka" in her film ''Karam'' (2005) as she wanted to concentrate on her acting career. She later sang the song live on the TV program ''[[Sa Re Ga Ma Pa]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka sings live on TV! |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-09-24/tv/28237147_1_playback-piggy-chops-priyanka-chopra|work=The Times of India|date=24 September 2010|accessdate=4 April 2011}}</ref>
[[File:Priyanka Chopra at Reliance Digital.JPG|thumb|left|Chopra promoting her single "[[In My City]]" at the Reliance Digital Store in November 2012.]]
In August 2011, Chopra signed a worldwide [[Sound recording and reproduction|recording]] agreement with [[Universal Music Group]], and [[DesiHits]]. [[Troy Carter (Coalition Media Group)|Troy Carter]], CEO of Atom Factory, and who also manages [[Lady Gaga]], was signed by Chopra to manage her music career.<ref name=HR1>{{cite news|title=Universal Music Group Signs Bollywood Star Priyanka Chopra to Global Deal|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/universal-music-group-signs-bollywood-219569|work=Hollywood Reporter|author=Bhushan, Nyay |date=5 August 2011|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref> Her first album will be released by [[Interscope Records]] in North America and by [[Island Records]] elsewhere. [[Jimmy Iovine]], chairman of [[Interscope-Geffen-A&M]] records stated, "Pop music has always had a love affair with Indian culture, and with Priyanka's unique talent and experience, we have the opportunities to push the boundaries of popular culture."<ref name=um>{{cite news|title=Universal Music Group (UMG) & Desi Hits Sign International Bollywood Superstar Priyanka Chopra to Global Recording Agreement |url=http://www.universalmusic.com/corporate/detail/841 |publisher=[[Universal Music Group]] |date=5 August 2011|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref>

Chopra spent time in [[Los Angeles]] to work with her record label to complete the album. She has collaborated with artists such as [[Sam Watters]], Matthew Koma, [[Jay Sean]] and [[record producer|producer]] [[RedOne]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Bollywood Star Priyanka Chopra In The Studio With RedOne|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/bollywood/news/a392157/bollywood-star-priyanka-chopra-in-the-studio-with-redone.html|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|author=Baker, Steven |date=7 July 2012|accessdate=30 November 2012}}</ref> The album, in which she sings in English,<ref name=um/> is currently in the final stages of [[audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]] and production and is scheduled to release at the end of December 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Priyanka Chopra unveils the first look of her debut music album|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?ID=265680&subcatg=&keyword=music&nid=265680|publisher=NDTV|author=Sharma, Sarika |date=11 September 2012|accessdate=12 September 2012}}</ref> Her first [[single (music)|single]], "[[In My City]]", debuted in America on 13 September on the [[NFL Network]]'s [[Thursday Night Football]], 12 hours after it was released in India.<ref name=rel>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Music/Priyanka-Chopra-to-release-debut-song-for-Indian-fans-first/Article1-926437.aspx |title=Priyanka Chopra to release debut song for Indian fans first |publisher=''Hindustan Times'' |author=Singh, Prashant |date=8 September 2012|accessdate=14 September 2012}}</ref> The song, featuring [[rapping|rapper]] [[Will.i.am]], was produced by RedOne and was said to be inspired by the many cities that she lived in while growing up, and her journey from a small-town girl to a celebrity.<ref name=inspire/><ref name="hollywoodreporter1">{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra's First Single to Debut on NFL's 'Thursday Night Kickoff'|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/priyanka-chopras-first-single-debut-365449|author=Bhushan, Nyay |publisher=''Hollywood Reporter''|date=25 August 2012|accessdate=13 September 2012}}</ref> "In My City" trended at number one on [[Twitter]] a few minutes after release.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2012-09-13/news/33816957_1_atom-factory-priyanka-chopra-troy-carter|title=Priyanka Chopra releases single 'In my City', trends to number one position on Twitter|author=Raghavendra, Nandini |date=13 September 2012|accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref> The song was certified [[list of music recording certifications|triple platinum]] in India.<ref>{{cite news|title= Priyanka Chopra all set for club crawl|url=http://www.asianage.com/life-and-style/pc-s-all-set-club-crawl-906 |date=30 October 2012|publisher=''[[The Asian Age]]'' |accessdate=8 November 2012}}</ref> Following the release of her first single, Chopra recorded an [[Electronic dance music]] track with the American [[disc jockey]] and producer duo [[The Chainsmokers]] called "[[Erase (song)|Erase]]" as a [[Guest appearance|featured artist]]. Prior to its official release on [[Beatport]], a sneak preview of the song was made available on the music website [[SoundCloud]] which garnered over 25,000 plays within a day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/%22priyanka-chopra-features-in-chainsmokers-album%22/1034894/ |title=Priyanka Chopra features in 'Chainsmokers' album |publisher=''[[The Indian Express]]'' |date=22 November 2012 |accessdate=27 November 2012}}</ref>

===Television and stage performances===
[[File:IPL 5 pohoto(10).jpg|thumb|right|Chopra performing at the 5th edition of Indian Premier League in Chennai]]
In 2010, Chopra became a television host with the reality show ''[[Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi (season 3)|Khatron Ke Khiladi]]'' on the [[Colors (TV channel)|Colors]] TV channel, replacing Akshay Kumar. She performed most of the stunts herself.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka to leave for Brazil on Aug 15 for Khatron Ke Khiladi|url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/jul/190710-Priyanka-Chopra-Brazil-August-15-Khatron-Ke-Khiladi.htm|publisher=''[[Mid Day]]''|date=19 July 2010|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> The show eventually beat the opening ratings of the previous two seasons.<ref>{{cite web|author=Indo-Asian News Service |title=Khatron Ke Khiladi 3 TRPs break record |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Khatron-Ke-Khiladi-3-opening-TRP-ratings-breaks-record/Article1-600561.aspx|work=Hindustan Times|date=15 September 2010|accessdate=28 September 2010}}</ref> Her work as a TV show host was praised and also earned her the [[Indian Telly Awards|Indian Telly Award]] for Most Impactful Debut on Television.<ref>{{cite news|title=The Tenth Indian Telly Awards|url=http://tellyawards.indiantelevision.com/y2k10/winners.php|publisher=Telly Awards|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref>

Chopra is a regular stage performer and has participated in various concerts and award ceremonies.
She took part in a concert tour titled ''Temptations 2004'' and performed alongside other Bollywood actors and actresses, including [[Shahrukh Khan]], [[Saif Ali Khan]], [[Rani Mukerji]], [[Preity Zinta]] and [[Arjun Rampal]] in nineteen stage shows worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|title=Temptation 2004|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/Temptation-2004-imagegallery-events-jdwmFcichfa.html?html=5|publisher=sify|accessdate=19 March 2011}}</ref> In 2011, Chopra participated in the Friendship Concert along with [[Shahid Kapoor]] and Shahrukh Khan, celebrating 150 years of the India-South Africa friendship in [[Durban]], South Africa. The concert was hosted by actor [[Anil Kapoor]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Celebrities galore at 150th anniversary in SA|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/gupshup/2011/anil-shahrukh-priyanka-anniversary-050111.html |publisher=oneindia.in|date=5 January 2011|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> In 2012, Chopra performed at the opening ceremony of the 5th edition of [[Indian Premier League]] alongside [[Amitabh Bachchan]], [[Salman Khan]], [[Kareena Kapoor]] and international pop star [[Katy Perry]]. The Event was held in [[M. A. Chidambaram Stadium]], [[Chennai]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Datta, Dwaipayan |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/cricket/ipl-2012/news/IPL-2012-Opening-Ceremony-IPL-party-begins-with-star-studded-opening-ceremony-as-fans-swoon/articleshow/12524604.cms |title=IPL 2012 Opening Ceremony: IPL party begins with star-studded opening ceremony as fans swoon|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=4 April 2012|accessdate=14 September 2012}}</ref> Like the IPL opening nite, Pune had its own opening nite for its newly constructed [[Pune International Cricket Centre|Sahara Stadium]] in which Chopra performed along with other Bollywood actresses, including [[Bipasha Basu]], [[Dia Mirza]], Preity Zinta, [[Neha Dhupia]], [[Jacqueline Fernandez]] and [[Sameera Reddy]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Gaur, Shelly |url=http://www.internationalreporter.com/News-10790/priyanka-chorpa-to-perform-in-pune-today.html |title=Priyanka Chorpa to perform in Pune today |publisher=International Reporter |date=8 April 2012 |accessdate=14 September 2012}}</ref>

In 2007, Chopra returned to the Miss India pageant as a judge for the first time. She stated, "Miss India will always remain special. That's where it all started for me. And maybe that's where it would've ended if I hadn't won the crown."<ref name=mi-special>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/News-Feed/MirchMasala/Miss-India-is-special-for-Priyanka/Article1-214555.aspx |title=Miss India is special for Priyanka |publisher=''Hindustan Times'' |date=9 April 2007 |accessdate=15 March 2012}}</ref> She came back again to Miss India in 2009 as a performer, and also became a judge at [[Miss World 2009]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Miss+World+will+not+change+the+world:+Priyanka+Chopra/1/74933.html |title=Miss World will not change the world: Priyanka Chopra |publisher=''India Today'' |date=14 December 2009 |accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Priyanka+is+my+lucky+charm:+Pooja/1/74621.html |title=Priyanka is my lucky charm: Pooja |publisher=''India Today'' |date=11 December 2009 |accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/News-Feed/InterviewsCinema/With-seven-awards-it-s-been-a-fantastic-start-Priyanka-Chopra/Article1-397523.aspx |title=With seven awards, it's been a 'fantastic' start: Priyanka Chopra |publisher=''Hindustan Times'' |date=6 April 2009 |accessdate=16 March 2012}}</ref>

===Column writing===
Chopra started writing a news column titled "The Priyanka Chopra Column" for ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' in 2009. She expressed joy at Participating in the project, saying, "I<U+2019>m a private person and never thought that I could express my feelings. But strangely enough, whenever I sat down to write this column, my inner most thoughts came to the fore."<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra turns 50 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Lifestyle/CelebWatch/Priyanka-Chopra-turns-50/Article1-512840.aspx|publisher=''Hindustan Times'' |author=Chopra, Priyanka |date=26 February 2102|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> In March 2009 she decided to personally interact with some readers who had sent their feedback on her weekly column. "This is my way of proving to my fans that indeed it<U+2019>s I who writes the column and reads the hundreds of letters they send me each week," said Chopra.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hi, it<U+2019>s Priyanka |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/News-Feed/Entertainment/Hi-it-s-Priyanka/Article1-388701.aspx|publisher=''Hindustan Times''|author=Neha Sharma and Garima Sharma|date=12 March 2009|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> She still writes sporadically for the paper. In August 2012, she wrote a column titled, "No woman in Mumbai feels safe any longer", published by ''The Times of India'', in which she discussed the death of 25-year-old Pallavi Purkayastha. Chopra also expressed how strongly she felt about the safety of women in the city. She wrote, "We have to, in whichever way we can, ensure that what happened with Pallavi does not happen again... we need to remind ourselves that we women today are a vital contributor to the growth of the new India."<ref name="TOI coulmn">{{cite news|title=No woman in Mumbai feels safe any longer: Priyanka Chopra |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-19/news-interviews/33262312_1_independence-day-mumbai-young-girl|publisher=''The Times of India''|author=Chopra, Priyanka |date=19 August 2012|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref>

===Endorsements===
Chopra has a number of endorsements and is one of the top paid Bollywood actresses in this respect.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-03-13/news-interviews/28685915_1_ad-revenue-ad-vantage-endorsement|title=Ad-vantage B-Town bombshells|work=The Times of India|date=13 March 2011|accessdate=20 March 2011}}</ref> In 2009, a survey conducted by [[TAM Media Research|AdEx India]] declared her as the queen of brand endorsements, ranking second on the list of top-notch [[brand ambassador]]s of 2008.<ref name=queen>{{cite news |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/priyanka-chopra-queen-of-endorsements-in-2008/84982-8.html|title=Priyanka Chopra queen of endorsements in 2008|publisher=CNN-IBN|date=10 February 2009|accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref> In 2011, she was signed to become the brand ambassador of Blenders Pride Fashion Tour.<ref name=bpft>{{cite press release|title=Blenders Pride Fashion Tour 2011 |url=http://www.afaqs.com/news/company_briefs/index.html?id=50651_Blenders+Pride+Fashion+Tour+2011 |publisher=Blender's Pride |quote=Bollywood Diva and fashion icon Priyanka Chopra as the Brand Ambassador Blender's Pride Fashion Tour 2011 |date=22 July 2011|accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref> She has also represented other brands including [[Lux (soap)|Lux]], [[Pond's Creams|Ponds]], [[Sunsilk]], [[Hero Honda]], [[Nokia]], [[Tag Heuer]], J. Hampsted, [[Virgin Comics]],<ref name=queen/> [[Gitanjali Group|Asmi]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra dazzles in Dubai on Tuesday |url=http://gulfnews.com/arts-entertainment/celebrity/priyanka-chopra-dazzles-in-dubai-on-tuesday-1.1044378 |publisher=''[[Gulf News]]''|date=4 July 2012|accessdate=2 December 2012}}</ref> [[Levi's|Levis]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra Unveils Levi's Jeans Change Your World Campa |url=http://daily.bhaskar.com/album/GAL-album-216-priyanka-chopra-unveils-levis-jeans-change-your-world-campa.html |publisher=''[[Daily Bhaskar]]''|date=27 June 2012|accessdate=2 December 2012}}</ref> [[Instant coffee|Bru]],<ref>{{cite news|title=HUL signs Priyanka Chopra and Shahid Kapoor as brand ambassadors for Bru |url=http://www.afaqs.com/news/story/29384_HUL-signs-Priyanka-Chopra-and-Shahid-Kapoor-as-brand-ambassadors-for-Bru |publisher=afaqs!|date=17 January 2011|accessdate=2 December 2012}}</ref> [[Nikon]],<ref name=pepsi/> [[Garnier]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/news/type/view/id/1313433/sorttype//Priyanka+Chopra+to+be+brand+ambassador+of+Garnier |title=Priyanka Chopra to be brand ambassador of Garnier|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|date=30 January 2012|accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref> [[Dabur]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Dabur signs Priyanka Chopra as brand ambassador for hair oil |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2012-09-03/news/33563464_1_brand-ambassador-dabur-amla-hair-oil-dabur-india|publisher=''Economic Times''|date=9 September 2012|accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref> [[Videocon]] Digital Direct Boradcast <ref>{{cite web |title=Priyanka Chopra has got another brand under her belt |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?Section=Movies&ID=ENTEN20120207700&subcatg=MOVIESINDIA&keyword=bollywood&nid=236571 |publisher=NDTV|date=27 June 2012|accessdate=9 September 2012}}</ref> and [[Pepsi]].<ref name=pepsi>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra makes a comeback as Pepsi's brand ambassador |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2012-09-12/news/33789513_1_brand-ambassador-priyanka-chopra-pepsico |work=The Economic Times|date=12 September 2012|accessdate=12 September 2012}}</ref>

==Philanthropy==
Chopra supports various charities including NDTV's ''Greenathon'', an initiative to support eco-friendliness and look into lack of electricity in rural villages.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/mp/2011/06/09/stories/2011060951860400.htm |title=Metro Plus Kochi / People : Green agenda |publisher=''The Hindu'' |date=9 June 2011 |accessdate=28 September 2011 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref> She featured in an animated video alongside children to support the cause.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/news/2010/priyanka-animated-music-video-150210.html|title=priyanka chopra in an animated video |publisher=oneindia.in |date=15 February 2010|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> In February 2005, Chopra participated in the ''HELP! Telethon Concert'' to help raise money for the victims of the [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake]] with other Bollywood actors.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050208/asp/nation/story_4351693.asp |title=Bollywood unites to present caring face |publisher=''The Telegraph'' |date=8 February 2005 |accessdate=13 December 2011}}</ref> In 2006,  an auction on eBay India opened bids to help the auction winner spend a day with Chopra. All proceeds from the auction were donated to a NGO called Nanhi Kali which helps to educate the girl children in rural and urban India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.oneindia.in/2006/08/10/priyanka-chopra-is-ebay-style-diva-2006-1155224070.html|title=Priyanka Chopra is eBay Style Diva 2006|publisher=oneindia.in|date=10 August 2006|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> In 2007, she visited troops in historic Tenga in eastern India to boost the morale of the [[Jawan]] troops for a special episode on the NDTV show, ''Jai Jawan'', celebrating the country's 60th anniversary of independence.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.radiosargam.com/films/archives/6139/event-photos-priyanka-chopra-on-ndtv-jai-jawan.html |title=Event Photos: Priyanka Chopra on NDTV Jai Jawan |publisher=Radio Sargam |date=15 August 2007|accessdate=22 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/video/player/jai-jawan/jai-jawan-with-priyanka-chopra/16141|title=Jai Jawan with Priyanka Chopra |publisher=NDTV|date=15 August 2007|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> In 2009, Chopra shot a documentary for the organization, Alert India, to spread awareness about [[leprosy]]. Later, the documentary was presented at a charity dinner which was hosted by Chopra herself.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/news/2009/priyanka-leprosy-awareness-061109.html|title=Priyanka Chopra spreads awareness on leprosy|publisher=oneindia.in|date=6 November 2009|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref>

Chopra often speaks out for women's issues, against [[infanticide|female infanticide]] and [[feticide]], and in support of education for all girls.<ref>{{cite web|title=Girls can and will be stronger than boys: Priyanka Chopra |url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/entertainment/girls-can-and-will-be-stronger-than-boys-priyanka-chopra_100227294.html |publisher=Thaindian News|date=3 August 2009|accessdate=2 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Educating the girl child is most important |url=http://madeinatlant.powweb.com/priyanka_chopra/interview2.htm |publisher=Atlantis International |date=|accessdate=2 December 2012}}</ref> In 2010, she joined hands with "Wave", a philanthropic organization that works for the cause of women. She was one of several celebrities who created promotional messages in favor of the organisation.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/mobile/report.php?n=1347298&p=0|title=Bollywood celebrities to support Pearls Wave intitiave on women against violence|publisher=''Daily News and Analysis''|accessdate=5 September 2012|date=13 February 2010}}</ref> She also launched a "Save the Girl child" campaign through which she urged couples not to go in for abortion when they find out that they are soon to become the parents of a baby girl.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra kicks off 'Save Girl Child' campaign |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/etc/priyanka-chopra-kicks-off-save-girl-child-campaign_612977.html|publisher=Zee News|date=10 March 2012|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> She was appointed as a [[UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador]] in 2010, joining Bollywood actor Amitabh Bachchan and actress [[Sharmila Tagore]] for supporting UNICEF<U+2019>s work regarding children all over the world. She had already been working with UNICEF since 2008. During that time, she has recorded public service announcements and participated in media panel discussions to promote children's rights and education of girls.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unicef.org/media/media_55497.html|title=Bollywood Actress Priyanka Chopra becomes UNICEF National Ambassador |publisher=[[UNICEF]] |date=10 August 2010|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Priyanka for girls' education as UNICEF ambassador|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/priyanka-for-girls-education-as-unicef-ambassador/658577/|publisher=''The Indian Express''|date=10 August 2010|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref>

[[File:Priyanka Chopra walks for Manish Malhotra & Shaina NC's show for CPAA 01.jpg|thumb|left|Chopra with designer Manish Malhotra at the CPAA charity fashion show in July 2012]]
In 2012, Chopra appeared with [[Priya Dutt]] at the launch of ''Awakening Youth'', a program to make mankind addiction free. She was a hit among the crowds and gave the audience a touching speech about the future of the youth of [[India]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra at Launch of "Awakening Youth 2012" (video) |url=http://www.thesundayindian.com/en/videos/774/ |publisher=The Sunday Indian|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> At the start the fourth edition of NDTV's ''Greenathon'', Chopra cleaned the [[Yamuna river]] in [[Agra]] in a symbolic gesture as part of an initiative to create awareness for environmental issues. She said, "This time we began our campaign from Agra because tourist inflow is maximum here. Taj Mahal is on the bank of river Yamuna, which has become a dumping zone of waste materials now. If we do not protect our environment our future will be dark." Model-actor [[Milind Soman]], politicians, environmental organizations, and school children joined her in the effort.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.internationalreporter.com/News-10936/priyanka-chopra-promotes-greenathon-campaign.html|title=Priyanka Chopra promotes Greenathon campaign |publisher=International Reporter|date=10 April 2012|accessdate=10 April 2012}}</ref> Chopra adopted a tigress named Durga at the [[Ranchi#Tourist attractions|Birsa biological park]] for the year 2011<U+2013>12, and then a lioness named Sundari for 2012<U+2013>13 from the same zoo. She sent a sum of {{INRConvert|2|l}} to the zoo authorities for the same.<ref>{{cite news|title=After tigress, Priyanka adopts lioness Sundari|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-06-02/ranchi/31983339_1_animal-adoption-zoo-authorities-lioness |publisher=''The Times of India''|date=2 June 2012|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> In July 2012, Chopra walked for designer [[Manish Malhotra]] and [[Shaina NC]]'s charity fashion show for NGO Cancer Patients Aid Association (CPAA) along with other celebrities like [[Ayushmann Khurrana]] to spread awareness about cancer.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mumbai fashion show spreads awareness about cancer|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/mumbai-fashion-show-spreads-awareness-about-cancer/1/203598.html |publisher=''India Today''|date=3 July 2012|accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref> Chopra pledged to donate her organs after death and promote organ donation as the Goodwill Ambassador of UNICEF. During her father's liver illness treatment at the [[University of Rochester Medical Center]] (URMC), she learned about the institution's organ transplant programs.<ref>{{cite news|title=URMC celebrates 20 years of liver transplants Bollywood star Priyanka Chopra to grace gala banquet as keynote speaker|url=http://www.indiatribune.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=9610:urmc-celebrates-20-years-of-liver-transplants-bollywood-star-priyanka-chopra-to-grace-gala-banquet-as-keynote-speaker&catid=25:community&Itemid=457|publisher=''[[India Tribune]]''|accessdate=9 October 2012}}</ref> She was invited to be the keynote speaker along with [[University of Pittsburgh Medical Center]]'s [[Thomas Starzl]], M.D., Ph.D., at the university's Bollywood themed 20th anniversary celebration of its Liver Transplant Program in October 2012, held in New York.<ref>{{cite web|title=Priyanka pledges to donate her organs|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-10/news-interviews/33736488_1_organ-donation-priyanka-chopra-pee-cee|author=Kadam, Prachi |work=The Times of India|date=10 September 2012|accessdate=21 September 2012}}</ref>

==Public image and personal life==
Chopra is considered one of the most popular Bollywood celebrities in India.<ref>{{cite news|title=Birthday Special: 30 Facts About Priyanka Chopra&nbsp;<U+2014> Page 5 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-birthday-special-priyanka-chopra/20120718.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|date=18 July 2012|accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref> She also has a reputation as one of the most desirable women in India, and has been described as a sex symbol.<ref>{{cite news|title=Top Bollywood sex symbols of all time|url=http://www.indiatribune.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=4730:top-bollywood-sex-symbols-of-all-time&catid=108:filmi-duniya&Itemid=472|publisher=''India Tribune''|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> Chopra is also known as a style icon in India.<ref name=bpft/><ref name=dress/> Designers Falguni & Shane Peacock noted, "She is comfortable in her own skin and looks ravishing in whatever she wears, be it a bikini, short or long dress or even a saree."<ref>{{cite news|title=The femme fatales of Bollywood! |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report_the-femme-fatales_1389614|publisher=''Daily News and Analysis''|date=30 May 2010|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref> As her most distinctive physical features, Chopra's figure, eye colour, and especially her "bee-stung" lips have been cited by the media as her trademark.<ref name=AskMen>{{cite news|title=Top 99 Women of 2012&nbsp;<U+2014> Why Is Priyanka Chopra No. 70?|url=http://www.askmen.com/specials/2012_top_99/70-priyanka-chopra.html|publisher=[[AskMen]] |accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref> She is often referred to by the nickname "Piggy Chops", which was given to her by co-stars on the set of the film ''[[Bluffmaster!]]'' in 2005.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka bored of Piggy Chops|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-10-28/news-interviews/28257294_1_priyanka-chopra-priyanka-fans-piggy-chops|publisher=''The Times of India''|author=Sharma, Smrity |date=28 October 2010|accessdate=14 March 2011}}</ref> Chopra does not come from a film background, and announces herself as a self-made woman.<ref name=self>{{cite news|title=I am a self-made woman: Priyanka Chopra |url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2010/20100411/spectrum/main10.htm |publisher=''Tribune India''|author=Bandyopadhyay, Bohni |date=11 April 2010|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[The Express Tribune]]'' she explained that her journey has been a learning experience as she came into the film industry without knowing anyone.<ref>{{cite news|title=Great time for Indian actresses: Priyanka Chopra |url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/391649/great-time-for-indian-actresses-priyanka-chopra/|publisher=''Express Tribune''|date=10 June 2012|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref>

She often ranks high on lists of most powerful, popular, or attractive Indian celebrities. In 2006, and again in 2012, the UK magazine ''[[Eastern Eye (newspaper)|Eastern Eye]]'' ranked her first on their list of "Asia's Sexiest Women".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/sep/20sld1.htm |title=Asia's sexiest women |publisher=Rediff.com |date=20 September 2006 |accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/sep/20sld5.htm |title=Asia's sexiest women <U+2212> 1. Priyanka Chopra |publisher=Rediff.com |date=20 September 2006 |accessdate=29 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=|url=http://www.easterneye.eu/news.html?groupId=7&newsId=1169 |title=World's sexiest Asian women 2012 list out in Eastern Eye |publisher=''[[Eastern Eye (newspaper)|Eastern Eye]]'' |date=6 December 2012|accessdate=6 December 2012}}</ref> Also in 2006, an eBay online poll crowned her "Style Diva of the Year".<ref>{{cite web|title=Priyanka Chopra is eBay India Style Diva |url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/news/2006/priyanka-chopra-110806.html |publisher=oneindia.in|date=11 August 2006|accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref> In 2008 she was chosen as "Godess of Atlantis" at the mega inauguration function of Dubai's [[Atlantis, The Palm]] on [[Palm Jumeirah]] where she did the gracious act of introducing 'Atlantis Rising', an aerial ballet of fireworks, performed by Grucci family.<ref>{{cite web|title=Priyanka chosen to be the 'Goddess of Atlantis'|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/%22priyanka-chosen-to-be-the-goddess-of-atlantis%22/389291/|publisher=''The Indian Express''|date=22 November 2008|accessdate=22 November 2012}}</ref> Chopra occupied the top slot in Rediff.com's annual listing of "Bollywood's Best Actress" in 2009<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com|title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2009|date=31 December 2009|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-best-actresses-of-2009/20091231.htm|accessdate=29 November 2012}}</ref> and also featured in the list for the years 2005, 2006 and 2008.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com|title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2005|date=23 December 2005|url=http://specials.rediff.com/yearend/2005/dec/23yend9.htm|accessdate=19 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com|title=Bollywood's top actresses, 2006|date=25 August 2006|url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/25sd4.htm|accessdate=29 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rediff.com|title=Bollywood's best actresses, 2008|url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2009/jan/05slide9-best-actresses-2008.htm|accessdate=29 November 2012}}</ref> In 2009 she was ranked by Rediff.com as the third most powerful actress in India.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Most Powerful Actresses in India|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2009/apr/06sli3-most-powerful-actresses-in-india.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|date=6 April 2009|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> In January 2011, she placed fifth on Rediff's list of "Top 10 Actresses of 2000<U+2013>2010".<ref name="RediffDecade">{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-top-10-bollywood-actresses-of-the-decade/20110105.htm|title=How The Decade Has Treated These Actresses|accessdate=2012-07-11|author=Verma, Sukanya|date=2011-01-05|publisher=Rediff.com}}</ref> She ranked 3rd in ''The Times of India'''s 50 most desirable women of 2010,<ref>{{cite web|title=Times 50 Most Desirable Women|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-01-09/news-interviews/28375785_1_nicole-faria-vidya-balan-preity-zinta|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=9 January 2011|accessdate=1 September 2012}}</ref> and ranked 4th for 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Times 50 Most Desirable Women of 2011 : The Winners|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Times-50-Most-Desirable-Women-of-2011-The-Winners/articleshow/11753716.cms|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=4 February 2012|accessdate=1 September 2012}}</ref> In 2011, she was declared by ''[[People (magazine)|People Magazine]]'' as "India's Best Dressed Woman of the year"<ref name=dress>{{cite web|title=Priyanka Chopra named India's Best Dressed|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?ID=ENTEN20110185689&keyword=bollywood&subcatg=MOVIESINDIA&nid=139642|publisher=NDTV|date=8 October 2011|accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref> and ''Maxim Magazine'' named her the "Hottest Girl of the year".<ref>{{cite web|title=Priyanka Chopra Is Maxim Hottest Girl 2011  (Interview video)|url=http://businessofcinema.com/videos/priyanka-chopra-is-maxim-hottest-girl-2011/41660 |publisher=Business Of Cinema|date=|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref> In April 2012, Chopra was declared as the Topmost influential Indian in the social media circuit by a survey conducted by ''[[Pinstorm|Pinstorm India]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka Chopra beats Big B, Sachin Tendulkar |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-04-04/news-interviews/31281205_1_priyanka-chopra-social-media-sachin-tendulkar|publisher=''The Times of India''|date=4 April 2012|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref>

Chopra has said that she is very close to her family and is grateful for what her family has sacrificed for her.<ref name=self/> Although known for her media friendly attitude, Chopra has always been evasive about her personal life. Concerning her online presence on Twitter she said, "One thing that I haven't done and never will is talking about my personal life."<ref>{{cite news|title=I'll never discuss my personal life online: Priyanka Chopra |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?Section=Movies&ID=ENTEN20100156954&subcatg=MOVIESINDIA&keyword=bollywood&nid=60473 |publisher=NDTV|date=18 October 2010|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref> However, she has maintained that when there's an announcement worth making, she will talk.<ref>{{cite news|title=I am very high headed: Priyanka Chopra |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-03/news-interviews/32509477_1_cliques-priyanka-chopra-bollywood |publisher=''The Times of India''|author=Saxena, Kashika |date=3 July 2012|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref> She lives with her family and dog named Brando.<ref>{{cite web|title=Birthday Special: 30 Facts About Priyanka Chopra&nbsp;<U+2014> Page 22|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-birthday-special-priyanka-chopra/20120718.htm|publisher=Rediff.com|date=18 July 2012|accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=There's me |url=http://www.iampriyankachopra.com/there_me.php |publisher=iampriyankachopra.com|accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref>

==Honours and awards==
{{See also|List of awards and nominations received by Priyanka Chopra}}
Among the film awards that Chopra has received are one [[National Award]] and four different [[Filmfare Awards]]. She won the [[National Film Award for Best Actress]] for ''[[Fashion (film)|Fashion]]'' (2008).<ref name=nat/> Her Filmfare awards are [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut]] for  ''[[Andaaz]]'' (2003),<ref name=ff1/> [[Filmfare Award for Best Performance in a Negative Role]] for ''[[Aitraaz]]'' (2004),<ref name=ff2/> [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]] for ''Fashion'',<ref name=ff3/> and [[Filmfare Critics Award for Best Actress]] for ''[[7 Khoon Maaf]]'' (2011).<ref name=ff4/>

Chopra has also been the recipient of various honours. She appeared on the cover of the inaugural issue of India's edition of ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim Magazine]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/news/type/view/id/5396/newsid/1174060 |title=Priyanka poses for inaugural cover of Maxim|publisher=Bollywood Hungama |date=30 December 2005 |accessdate=7 January 2012}}</ref> She was one of four Bollywood actors including [[Shah Rukh Khan]], [[Kajol]] and [[Hrithik Roshan]] whose miniature dolls were launched by [[Hasbro]] and UK-based Bollywood Legends Corporation.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dollywood Stars |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2006-09-10/news/27455458_1_bollywood-movies-uk-market-bollywood-stars |publisher=''The Economic Times''|author=Banerjee, Rajiv |date=10 September 2006|accessdate=7 September 2012}}</ref> In 2010, she became the first Indian actress to cast her foot impression at the famous [[Salvatore Ferragamo Museum]] in Florence, Italy. She also got her own custom-designed shoes from the Ferragamo house. With this honour, Chopra joined several Hollywood celebrities.<ref>{{cite news|title=Priyanka's foot stamp at Ferragamo museum |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/Priyanka's+foot+stamp+at+Ferragamo+museum!/1/83282.html |publisher=''India Today''|date=10 February 2010|accessdate=28 November 2012}}</ref> She received the Trailblazer Award from the South Asians in Media, Marketing and Entertainment Association "for her blazing trails in the U.S. for Indian entertainers as the first Bollywood actor to win a major record deal in the U.S., and her ongoing commitment and passion for continuous creative/artistic/personal achievement."<ref>{{cite web|title=2011 SAMMA Summit Announcements |url=http://www.sammaconference.org/|publisher=sammaconference.org |accessdate=17 September 2012}}</ref> In 2012, Chopra was honored with a "Punjabi Icon Award" at a [[Baisakhi]] celebration in Mumbai. She and the other recipients were chosen for their contributions in their respective fields.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.internationalreporter.com/News-10842/priyanka-chopra-gets-the-punjabi-icon-award.html |title=Priyanka Chopra Gets the Punjabi Icon Award |publisher=International Reporter|date=9 Apr 2012|accessdate=31 August 2012}}</ref>

